  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Rethinking Impact Factors: New Pathways in Journal Metrics\" by Cassidy R. Sugimoto et al. has made a significant mark in academic discourse, with eight citations demonstrating its influence across various scholarly venues.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The article \"Rethinking Impact Factors: New Pathways in Journal Metrics,\" authored by Cassidy R. Sugimoto and colleagues, has garnered notable academic attention since its publication. With eight citations cataloged in OpenAlex, this work contributes to a growing dialogue on the relevance and evaluation of journal metrics. Notably, it has been cited in prominent venues, including F1000Research and Nature, indicating its resonance within the academic community.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">This work stands out not only for its academic achievements but also for its potential societal importance, as evidenced by its presence within scholarly discussions across multiple countries, including the United States, Israel, and Germany. This geographic diversity of citations enhances the work's visibility and demonstrates its relevance across different research landscapes.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The article has sparked engagement among scholars, with citations including both articles and preprints, showcasing its influence at the cutting edge of research in journal metrics. The presence of preprints represents an active discourse among researchers who are eager to explore and validate the concepts presented in Sugimoto et al.'s work.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, the proven downstream reuse of its findings\u2014evidenced by eight instances of reuse\u2014demonstrates that the concepts and methodologies developed in this work are being integrated into further research. Such impacts exemplify a commitment to advancing the scholarly conversation around journal metrics and enhance its standing as a pivotal contribution to the field.</p>",
